text: The electoral district of West Launceston, sometimes referred to as Launceston West, was a single-member electoral district of the Tasmanian House of Assembly. It was based in the western suburbs of Launceston, Tasmania's second city. The seat was created in a redistribution ahead of the 1903 state election, and was abolished when the Tasmanian parliament adopted the Hare- Clark electoral model in 1909. ==Members for West Launceston== {| class="wikitable" |- !colspan="2"|Member!!Party!!Term |- | | Liberal | David Storrer | 1903 |- | | Liberal | Matthew Robinson | 1903–1906 |- | | Ind.
